libmpq
------------------------------------------
libmpq is a library which can be easily used in own applications to extract,
create or manipulate MoPaQ mpq archives.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-5.2.21-1
  cygwin-3.6.10-1
  libbz2-devel-1.0.8-2
  libbz2_1-1.0.8-2
  libmpq-devel-0.4.2-1bl2
  libmpq0-0.4.2-1bl2
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1
  python39-3.9.16-1
  zlib-devel-1.3.2-1
  zlib0-1.3.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  libbz2-devel-1.0.8-2
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2
  python39-3.9.16-1
  zlib-devel-1.3.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ge0rg/libmpq

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ge0rg/libmpq/archive/refs/tags/libmpq-0.4.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libmpq-0.4.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libmpq-0.4.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libmpq-0.4.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmpq-0.4.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmpq0-0.4.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmpq-devel-0.4.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/python39-libmpq-0.4.2-X.tar.xz

